revision.text:
{{nihongo|'''Ōmiya Hachiman Shrine'''|大宮八幡宮|Ōmiya-Hachimangū}} is a [[Shinto]] [[Jinja (Shinto)|shrine]] in [[Miki, Hyogo|Miki]], [[Hyōgo Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It is a [[Hachiman Shrine]] that was founded in 1111 and was rebuilt in 1585 after having burned down. <ref>[http://www.city.miki.lg.jp/bunka/hachimangu.html Omiya Hachiman Shrine] on the Miki City website (Japanese)</ref>
==Events== *Third Sunday in January: Oni-oi Shiki. *Second and third Saturdays and Sundays in October: Miki Autumn Harvest Festival.
==References== {{reflist}}
==Location== This shrine is near [[Miki Station (Shintetsu)|Miki station]] on the [[Shintetsu Ao Line|Ao Line]] of [[Kobe Electric Railway]].
{{coord missing|Japan}}
