inja (Shinto)|Jinja]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:]] in [[Miki, Hyogo|Miki]], [[Hyōgo Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It is a [[Hachiman ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:]] that was founded in 1111 and was rebuilt in 1585 after having burned down.<ref>[http://www.city.miki.lg.jp/bunka/hachimangu.html Omiya Hachiman ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:] on the Miki City website (Japanese)</ref>
== festival Deities == * Main deity - [[Emperor Ōjin]] * Associated deities - [[Mikumari|Kuninomikumari-no-Kami]], [[Amaterasu]], [[Susanoo|Susanoo-no-Mikoto]], [[Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto]], [[Kumano Kusu-kun-no-Mikoto]], [[Kamo-wake-ikazuchi-no-Kami|Kamo-wake-ikazuchi-no-Kami]], [[Nakatsu-no-Ono-no-Mikoto|Nakatomi-no-Mikoto]], [[Minakatatomi-no-Mikoto]]
== History == The founding date of the ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category: is unknown, but it was worshipped by the [[Bessho clan]], a branch of the [[Akamatsu clan]]. The ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category: was burned down during the [[Sengoku period (Japan)|Sengoku period]], but in the [[Edo period]], it received a red seal from the [[Tokugawa shogunate]]. The former ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category: rank was [[Gōsha]] (Village ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:).
== Main Structures == * main hall * Worship Hall * Auxiliary ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:s within the grounds ** Ōmiya Tenman ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:, Obiki Inari ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:, Fushimi Inari ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category: * Subsidiary ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:s within the grounds ** Toyotama-hime ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:, Harai-den, Bandō Inari ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:, Benzaiten ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category: * External ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:s ** Sanbonmatsu Inari ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:, Kotohira ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category: <gallery> File:Omiya-hachimangu Miki Hyogo07n4272.jpg|main hall File:Omiya-hachimangu Miki Hyogo02n4272.jpg|Worship Hall File:Omiya-hachimangu Miki Hyogo03n4272.jpg|Ōmiya Tenman ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category: File:Omiya-hachimangu Miki Hyogo01n4272.jpg|Stone Steps </gallery>
== Events and festivals == [[File:Omiya-hachimangu Miki Hyogo11n3200.jpg|thumb|Oni-chasing ceremony]] [[File:121007 Miki Autumn Harvest festival Miki Hyogo pref Japan02s5.jpg|thumb|festival]] * Oni-chasing ceremony (Setsubun Ritual) - 3rd Sunday in January * Tondo festival - January 15 * festival - Mid-October (Saturday and Sunday before Sports Day)
=== festival === The ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:'s festival held every October on the Saturday and Sunday before [[Sports Day]] is one of the three major festivals in [[Banshū]]. Eight floats from different districts are paraded and ascend the 85 steep stone steps to the ]][[Category:shrine pages to be written]][[Category:. The sight of the over one-ton floats being carried up the steps is impressive. Except for the Ōmura district, all seven other floats are tied with safety ropes during the ascent and descent. The festival floats are decorated with traditional crafts of [[carpentry]], [[embroidery]], [[wood carving]], and [[metal fittings]].
* Parade Order: Akashi Town, Shinmachi, Zen Suehiro, Shitamachi, Sakaemachi, Takagi, Hirata (only during the day), Ōmura (only during the day) * Parade Suspended: Shiroyama Town (due to a shortage of carriers)
Note: The Shinmachi float was destroyed by fire in 2007, and the parade was canceled that year and the following year. A new float storage was completed in February 2009, and the new float was unveiled in September of the same year. The parade resumed that year.
==== Floats ==== * Akashi Town Float - Flat roof, three tiers * Shinmachi Float - Curved roof, three tiers * Zen Suehiro Float - Flat roof, three tiers * Shitamachi Float - Curved roof, three tiers * Sakaemachi Float - Flat roof, three tiers * Shiroyama Town Float - Flat roof, three tiers (parade suspended) * Takagi Float - Flat roof, three tiers * Hirata Float - Flat roof, three tiers * Ōmura Float - Flat roof, three tiers
